# Streamlit Development Guidelines

## Code Style
- Use `st.set_page_config()` for page configuration
- Hide Streamlit default elements (header, footer, menu) with CSS
- Use `st.expander()` for collapsible sections
- Implement proper error handling with `st.error()` and `st.warning()`

## UI Components
- Use `st.columns()` for layout organization
- Implement `st.session_state` for data persistence
- Use `st.spinner()` for loading states
- Add `st.download_button()` for file exports

## Styling Guidelines
- Maintain blue color scheme: #1565C0 (primary), #90CAF9 (accent)
- Use custom CSS in `st.markdown()` with `unsafe_allow_html=True`
- Implement consistent button styling with shadows and hover effects
- Use card-based layouts for better visual hierarchy

## AI Integration
- Use `@retry` decorator for API reliability
- Implement proper error handling for rate limits
- Store API responses in session state for caching
- Use `st.spinner()` during AI generation

## File Structure
- Keep main app logic in `main()` function
- Separate AI functions from UI code
- Use descriptive function names and docstrings
- Implement proper input validation